<DOC><DOCNO> AP900817-0202 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-17-90 1528EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-FordProduction     08-17 0099</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Ford Production,0104</SECOND><HEAD>Ford Shuts Down Mustang Plant</HEAD><DATELINE>DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Ford Motor Co. will extend this week'sshutdown of its Dearborn assembly plant through next week becauseof a shortage of 2.3-liter engines for the Ford Mustang car, thecompany said Friday.   Ford spokesman Jay Meisenhelder said the shortage stemmed fromthe transfer of a slightly different 2.3-liter engine to thecompany's Lima, Ohio, engine plant. Previously the engine was madein Mexico.   The Dearborn plant was closed this week because of a shortage ofdealer orders.   There are about 2,100 hourly employees at the plant.</TEXT></DOC>